<h1>Academic Operations</h1>
<p>
Review of administrative workflows and institutional operating practices within higher education settings.
</p>
</section>

<section class="contact-card">
<h2>Objective</h2>
<p>
Assess academic administrative workflows for clarity, consistency, and operational effectiveness.
</p>

<h2>Context</h2>
<p>
Reflects higher education work involving cross-department coordination, administrative processing,
student-facing operations, and policy-linked workflow support.
</p>

<h2>Questions That Informed the Work</h2>
<ul>
<li>Which academic workflows experience the most delay or inconsistency?</li>
<li>Where do handoffs between departments create risk?</li>
<li>What administrative steps rely too heavily on manual effort?</li>
<li>How can process clarity improve service reliability?</li>
</ul>

<h2>Methods Used</h2>
<ul>
<li>Workflow analysis</li>
<li>Administrative process mapping</li>
<li>Approval path review</li>
<li>Operational documentation review</li>
</ul>

<h2>KPIs / Measures Used</h2>
<ul>
<li>Administrative cycle time</li>
<li>Number of manual handoffs</li>
<li>Approval completion timeliness</li>
<li>Error or rework volume</li>
</ul>

<h2>Stakeholders / Teams Benefited</h2>
<ul>
<li>Academic departments</li>
<li>Registrar and administrative staff</li>
<li>Student affairs and service functions</li>
<li>Institutional leadership</li>
</ul>

<h2>Estimated Timeline</h2>
<p>Approximately 3–6 weeks.</p>

<h2>Key Findings</h2>
<ul>
<li>Department workflows varied significantly</li>
<li>Manual processes created delays</li>
<li>Approval steps were not consistently documented</li>
</ul>

<h2>Recommendations</h2>
<ul>
<li>Map workflows across administrative units</li>
<li>Standardize recurring approval steps</li>
<li>Reduce manual handoffs where possible</li>
</ul>

<h2>Skills Demonstrated</h2>
<p>
Administrative workflow analysis, process review,
institutional operations assessment, and documentation.
</p>
</section>

